South Africa’s deep level gold mining industry will over the next 10 years almost entirely cease to exist (excluding Gold Fields’ South Deep mine). This is according to Nedbank precious metals analysts LEON ESTERHUIZEN and ARNOLD VAN GRAAN. And while this may be tragic news for the country it is not necessarily bad news not for the industry’s prominent role players should they successfully ramp up their efforts to build strong international portfolios, writes LAURA CORNISH.